Layout thrashing occurs when you repeatedly read and write DOM properties that trigger layout recalculation:

// BAD — forces layout on every read
elements.forEach(el => {
  el.style.width = container.offsetWidth + 'px'; // read → layout → write
});

// GOOD — batch reads, then batch writes
const width = container.offsetWidth; // read once
elements.forEach(el => {
  el.style.width = width + 'px'; // write only
});

Properties that trigger layout:
offsetWidth, offsetHeight, getBoundingClientRect(), scrollTop, clientWidth

Use requestAnimationFrame() to batch DOM writes.

Web Workers run JavaScript on a separate thread, preventing main thread blocking.

// main.js
const worker = new Worker('worker.js');
worker.postMessage({ data: largeArray });
worker.onmessage = (e) => console.log(e.data);

// worker.js
self.onmessage = (e) => {
  const result = heavyComputation(e.data);
  self.postMessage(result);
};

Use for:
• Heavy computations (sorting, filtering large datasets)
• Image/video processing
• Data parsing (large JSON, CSV)
• Encryption/hashing

Limitations: No DOM access, communication via postMessage (structured clone). Use Comlink for a nicer API.
